  "text": "The Kafka consumer group partition assignment strategies are implemented in the apache/kafka repository under the clients module. The core implementation includes: (1) RangeAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/RangeAssignor.java) - assigns partitions on a per-topic basis by dividing partitions into ranges and assigning them to consumers in lexicographic order, with support for rack-aware assignment; (2) RoundRobinAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/RoundRobinAssignor.java) - distributes partitions across all consumers using a round-robin approach, handling varying subscription patterns; (3) StickyAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/StickyAssignor.java) - preserves existing partition assignments during rebalancing while maintaining balanced distribution, implementing eager rebalancing protocol; and (4) CooperativeStickyAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/CooperativeStickyAssignor.java) - provides the same sticky assignment logic as StickyAssignor but supports cooperative rebalancing protocol for improved availability. These assignors extend AbstractPartitionAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractPartitionAssignor.java), which is the abstract base class providing common partition assignment functionality and utilities. StickyAssignor and CooperativeStickyAssignor additionally extend AbstractStickyAssignor (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractStickyAssignor.java), which implements the sticky assignment algorithm with support for rack-aware assignment, shared between both eager and cooperative implementations."
}

